¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssection{Definition} ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ Consider a distribution $p$ and a real-valued function $f$. ⦉

  ‖ The ❬distribution expectation❭ of $f$ ❬under❭ $p$ is the sum
    of the product of the results of $p$ and $f$ on the
    elements of the set. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssubsection{Notation} ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $A$ a finite set. ⦉

  ‖ Let $p: A → [0, 1]$ a distribution on a finite set $A$
    and let $f: A → 𝗥$ a function on $A$. ⦉

  ‖ The expectation of $f$ under $p$ is
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ ∑_{a ∈ A} p(a) f(a). ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

